    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Architecture Specification</title>
        <para>This data module provides the detailed architecture specification for the 
        AQUA-OS operating system, including the separation kernel design, partition 
        scheduling mechanisms, and memory management architecture.</para>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Separation Kernel Architecture</title>
          <para>The separation kernel provides the foundation for partitioning:</para>
          <para>- Hardware abstraction layer (HAL) for processor-specific features</para>
          <para>- Memory management unit (MMU) configuration and protection</para>
          <para>- Interrupt handling and vectoring</para>
          <para>- Context switching between partitions</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Partition Scheduling</title>
          <para>The scheduler implements fixed-priority, cyclic scheduling:</para>
          <para>- Major frame divided into partition windows</para>
          <para>- Non-preemptive execution within windows</para>
          <para>- Deterministic timing guarantees</para>
          <para>- Configurable via XML schedule tables</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Memory Management</title>
          <para>Memory is statically allocated at system initialization:</para>
          <para>- Partition memory regions defined in configuration</para>
          <para>- MMU enforces inter-partition isolation</para>
          <para>- No dynamic memory allocation in kernel</para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
